\section{Enabling HLO dumping}{


Dumping is driven by the XLA compiler's own dump mechanism, enabled through
the \code{XLA_FLAGS} environment variable. \strong{Two} flags are required:
\itemize{
\item \code{--xla_dump_hlo_as_text} -- dump the HLO in text form.
\item \verb{--xla_dump_to=<dir>} -- write the dump into \verb{<dir>}. \code{inspect_hlo()} reads
the HLO back from the files XLA writes here.
}

XLA reads \code{XLA_FLAGS} \strong{once, before the first compilation in an R process},
so both flags must be set at the very start of a fresh session, before any
\code{\link[=pjrt_compile]{pjrt_compile()}} or \code{\link[=pjrt_execute]{pjrt_execute()}} call:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode r">}}\preformatted{Sys.setenv(XLA_FLAGS = "--xla_dump_to=/tmp/hlo --xla_dump_hlo_as_text")
library(pjrt)
# ... build a program ...
inspect_hlo(prog)
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

